------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Assignment 1: 5 LKM Programming
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Credits
    Nicolas Appel
    Wenwen Chen
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Description
    - Output welcome messages when mod.ko is loaded
    - Output goodbye messages when mod.ko is unloaded
    - Output the number of processes in the system after the welcome message
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Documentation
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Installation instructions
    - Compile the module
      # make
    - Clean project
      # make clean
    - View the information of mod.ko
      # modinfo mod.ko
    - Load mod.ko
      # insmod mod.ko
    - View currently loaded kernel modules in the system
      # lsmod
    - Unload mod.ko
      # rmmod mod
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Additional Notes
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Questions
    - How to avoid system map adress casting to functions?
    - How do kernel header files declarations and system maps work together?
      (Why do some functions work out of box, e.g. printk, but some not, e.g. nr_processes?)
    - How can functions of the kernel be called in general?

